AGI - "There is a date" for the entry of the IDF troops to Rafah. The Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu announced that there was no victory without an operation in the city. According to the Israeli media, Netanyahu added that he had received a detailed update on talks in Cairo. "We are constantly working to achieve our goals," says Netanyahu, "first of all freeing all of our hostages and achieving total victory over Hamas. The victory over the Palestinian Islamist movement "requires entry to Rafah and the elimination of terrorist battalions there. This will be done, there is a date", said the Israeli Prime Minister in a video statement. According to Israel, Rafah remains one of the last strongholds of Hamas in the Gaza Strip.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
< blockquote
